# ================================================================================
# WHAT THIS FILE IS:
# Defines who is responsible for reviewing changes to different parts of the codebase.
#
# WHY YOU NEED IT:
# - Automatically assigns reviewers to pull requests
# - Documents code ownership and expertise
# - Shows you understand team collaboration (even for solo projects)
# - Required for branch protection rules in some orgs
#
# WHAT TO PUT IN IT:
# Patterns matching files/directories and the GitHub usernames of owners.
# Format: <pattern> <@username or @org/team>
# ================================================================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Default owner for everything
# Replace 'yourusername' with your GitHub username
# ---------------------------------------------------------
* @yourusername

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Specific ownership (examples for larger teams)
# ---------------------------------------------------------

# Documentation
# docs/ @yourusername

# CI/CD configuration
# .github/ @yourusername

# Core ML/AI code
# src/llm/ @yourusername
# src/retrieval/ @yourusername

# Infrastructure
# Dockerfile @yourusername
# docker-compose.yml @yourusername
